result.name: Satay King Causeway Bay

reviews.text:
This Satay King located right next to the busiest crossing of Causeway Bay area.  It's located on the 5th floor of The Goldmark, but as the entrance of the plaza is small, it's not easy to find the lift to the restaurant.
As this building located in the heart of the area, and this restaurant with a long glass windows, you can always see the busy street from here, and the open view from the restaurant is great too.
And their food is mediocre, you do not come here with great expectation.  After all, it just a chain restaurant.  But their price is budget friendly, so here still a good choice if you come with low budget

Foods pretty good here, always a go to option when I can’t think of what to eat. Their white curry pork chop is very good. I usually get it with rice or udon. The udon very isn’t as thick as the curry rice version. 

The soft shell crab is also pretty good. These are usually my two go to items to order here. Drinks here aren’t that good but I sometimes like getting the ribena drink.
One of my favorites! Highly recommended for those who are looking for great food but not too expensive. A coupon for your next visit will be given after paying your meal.

Waited almost 45mins for the pork chop rice with white curry and the soup, then it took another 30mins for the dessert, we did ask for several times about the missing dishes, but most of the staff just bypass our table or just gave us a short answer 'ok', without really following the request. The dishes finally turns out as they asked us to return the table. The food is just so so.
Food is good, price is reasonable.

I THINK THE OWNER/ EMPLOYER SHOULD KNOW THIS:

Service is EXTREMELY POOR. Poor attitudes of staff. No one response to your needs. Staff keep walking around collecting dirty dishes. They are annoying if you ask for hot water. Only given HOT TAP WATER 🚱 if you requested few times. Don't drink water given on table. BECAUSE it is TAP WATER 🚱even if you order HOT WATER. IT pour DIRECTLY FROM HOT WATER TAP WITHOUT BOILING👎👎👎. In Hong Kong, TAP WATER🚱 should not be drink directly from tap. IT MUST BE BOILED. Because it is full of germs & bacteria. You will get sick with diarrhea if you drink tap water.😷😷😷🚱🚱🚱

Satay, curry, white curry, Tom Yum Goong soup冬蔭功湯, etc in all kind of dishes. Taste ok. Only seats are too packed. And you must have to share table with strangers.❎❎❎
